Scenario = A real-world situation or problem example / A business problem for which we write queries or programs.


1: Employee Salary Analysis

Question

Find the names and salaries of employees who earn more than the average salary in the company.

Query
SELECT name, salary
FROM employees
WHERE salary > (
    SELECT AVG(salary)
    FROM employees
);


Result:

| name    | salary |
| ------- | ------ |
| John    | 60000  |
| Michael | 75000  |
| Sara    | 56000  |

==================


Scenario 2: Customer Orders without Matching Records

Question

Retrieve a list of customer names who have not placed any orders.

Query

SELECT c.customer_name
FROM customers c
LEFT JOIN orders o
ON c.customer_name = o.customer_name
WHERE o.order_id IS NULL;

Result:

| customer_name |
| ------------- |
| John Doe      |
| Jane Smith    |
| Alice Johnson |
| NULL          |
| Robert Brown  |


===========


3: Product Sales Summary
Question

Display the total sales amount for each product.

Query
SELECT product_name, price AS total_sales_amount
FROM products;


