4: Department-Wise Employee Count
Question

List each department name with the number of employees working in it.

Query

SELECT d.department_name,
COUNT(e.employee_id) AS employee_count
FROM departments d
LEFT JOIN employees e
ON d.department_id = e.department_id
GROUP BY d.department_name;

Result:

| department_name | employee_count |
| --------------- | -------------- |
| HR              | 2              |
| Finance         | 2              |
| IT              | 1              |
| Marketing       | 0              |


===========

5: Top 3 Highest Sales
Question

Find the top 3 highest sales transactions.

Query
SELECT *
FROM sales
ORDER BY amount DESC
LIMIT 3;

Result:

| sale_id | customer_id | amount  | sale_date  |
| ------- | ----------- | ------- | ---------- |
| 3       | 103         | 7000.00 | 2023-03-17 |
| 5       | 105         | 6000.00 | 2023-03-19 |
| 2       | 102         | 5500.00 | 2023-03-16 |

============

6: Calculate Employee Salary Ranks by Department
Question

Write a query to display each employee’s name, department name, salary, and their salary rank within their respective department.

Query
SELECT 
    e.name,
    d.department_name,
    e.salary,
    RANK() OVER (
        PARTITION BY d.department_name
        ORDER BY e.salary DESC
    ) AS salary_rank
FROM employees e
INNER JOIN departments d
ON e.department_id = d.department_id;

Result:

| name    | department_name | salary | salary_rank |
| ------- | --------------- | ------ | ----------- |
| John    | HR              | 60000  | 1           |
| Sara    | HR              | 56000  | 2           |
| Emily   | Finance         | 48000  | 1           |
| David   | Finance         | 49000  | 1           |
| Michael | IT              | 75000  | 1           |


===========










